 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jairoc4549>jairoc4549</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/27/03 4:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> If you are a current member then your children can still join the tribe you just need to send in your information. The registration as I understand it is closed to those not already in the tribe, but open to children of those in the tribe. Hope that helps. <br>
Joy Porter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=escanaba>escanaba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(9/3/03 8:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> Dear Frank<br>
The first response you received is correct. <br>
Children under 18 may enroll in the tribe.<br>
You will need birth records to verify your descendency.<br>
If your parents are enrolled your children may use the available<br>
records from them to trace/document their ancestory.<br>
If you  need some help on the genealogy issues let me know and I will help.<br>
<br>
Ron Powers<br>
Escanaba<br>
chief49829@yahoo.com<br>
<br>
P.S my goal for the next election is to open the rolls and take care of our FAMILY FIRST. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frankparker>FrankParker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(9/15/03 7:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Membership</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the response Ron. My Parents are indeed members but I am not (due to the closure of the rolls) - are you saying that I could have my Mother take care of the membership of my daughters?<br>
Frank<br>
<br>
And I agree - Family First! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sibdeb>sibdeb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(9/15/03 6:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> My father is a member of the tribe, as was his father and his father before him.  I was not made aware that I was eligible until 1999, but by then the rolls were closed.  My 3 brothers and I have been checking on the status every month or so, but no change.  Could someone possibly tell me why the rolls are closed to adults?  My brothers and I are quite disappointed that we are not able to join.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Thanx. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sidebyrnes>sidebyrnes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(12/31/03 1:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> My mother is a card holding member (not living in the 7 county area) and I attempted to late to enroll as I had turned 18 already when the rolls were closed. Can my children, however, be enrolled through my mother somehow? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bosco1955>bosco1955</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(2/12/04 1:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> My husband, his sister and all nieces and nephew are card carrying members of the Soo band of the Chippewa Indians. Unfortunately, because of my husbands negligence my children were not enrolled and never received their Indian card. Both children are over the age of 18. I find it quite frustrating  that due to circumstances that are no fault of theirs that my girls will be denied their birth rite as will their children. Is this some scam to keep people of Indian descent from claiming their heritage? If the proper papers can be provided then how can they be denied? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCC0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saulttribe>saulttribe</A></span><br> Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(2/17/04 9:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   enrollment</span><hr size=1> It doesn't make any sence to me! I have three children. The oldest had gotten married. I had asked her for a copy of her birth certificate and by the time I got a copy enrollment was closed. The other two are enrolled. The tribe has my file with all the documents they need. My father was a member as my brother. It isn't like you are trying to enroll a stranger. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsaulttribe.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jan@saulttribe>Jan</A></span><br> Posts: 9<br> <font color=#000000>(3/16/04 4:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Membership still closed???</span><hr size=1> 2 of my siblings didn't enroll... due to the lifestyles they were living. Alcohol had taken over their lives. Now, they have been sober for years and regret not being enrolled. The other 4 of us are however enrolled... though one of my brothers went in passing at the age of 43. <br>
<br>
We are thankful for the tribe helping with the burial costs... but I have tried to help my younger brother get enrolled... as he has been trying for years... and as tasteless as this seems... I asked the tribe what it would hurt if they took the brother who went in passings membership and allowed my younger brother to become enrolled. Nothing... zip! <br>
<br>
I can understand to a degree why the tribe has cut off enrollment, but yet this kids under the age of 18 seem to have less BQ than us older folks. That's the part I will never understand!<br>
<br>
Jan  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=35.topic"> <img src="http://www.saulttribe-nsn.gov/medicinew.jpg" border=0></a><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=35.topic"> <img src="http://www.saulttribe-nsn.gov/medicinew.jpg" border=0> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/pastel/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.threadControl?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/pastel/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsaulttribefrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="saulttribefrm1">Announcements<option value="saulttribefrm2">General Discussion<option value="sa